<figure class="lorenz-lens">
  <figcaption>Lorenz curve and the Gini coefficient (conceptual diagram)</figcaption>
  <div class="lorenz-lens-grid">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 240 240" role="img" aria-label="Lorenz curve diagram with equality line and shaded Gini area">
      <defs>
        <linearGradient id="lorenzFill" x1="0" x2="1" y1="0" y2="1">
          <stop offset="0%" stop-color="rgba(207,154,51,0.22)" />
          <stop offset="100%" stop-color="rgba(161,75,34,0.10)" />
        </linearGradient>
      </defs>

      <rect x="12" y="12" width="216" height="216" rx="14" fill="rgba(255,250,242,0.88)" stroke="rgba(28,49,70,0.12)" />

      <line x1="24" y1="216" x2="216" y2="216" stroke="rgba(28,49,70,0.35)" stroke-width="2" />
      <line x1="24" y1="216" x2="24" y2="24" stroke="rgba(28,49,70,0.35)" stroke-width="2" />

      <path
        d="M24 216 L216 24 C160 170 90 216 24 216 Z"
        fill="url(#lorenzFill)"
        opacity="0.9"
      />

      <line
        x1="24"
        y1="216"
        x2="216"
        y2="24"
        stroke="rgba(207,154,51,0.95)"
        stroke-width="2.5"
        stroke-dasharray="6 6"
      />

      <path
        d="M24 216 C90 216 160 170 216 24"
        fill="none"
        stroke="rgba(54,91,84,0.95)"
        stroke-width="3"
      />

      <circle cx="24" cy="216" r="3.6" fill="rgba(28,49,70,0.55)" />
      <circle cx="216" cy="24" r="3.6" fill="rgba(28,49,70,0.55)" />

      <text x="26" y="232" font-size="10" fill="rgba(22,36,50,0.7)">0</text>
      <text x="210" y="232" font-size="10" fill="rgba(22,36,50,0.7)">1</text>
      <text x="12" y="30" font-size="10" fill="rgba(22,36,50,0.7)">1</text>
      <text x="12" y="220" font-size="10" fill="rgba(22,36,50,0.7)">0</text>

      <text x="70" y="236" font-size="10" fill="rgba(22,36,50,0.7)">Cumulative population share</text>
      <text
        x="14"
        y="160"
        font-size="10"
        fill="rgba(22,36,50,0.7)"
        transform="rotate(-90 14 160)"
      >
        Cumulative income share
      </text>
    </svg>

    <div class="lorenz-lens-notes">
      <h3>How to read it</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>The dashed line is perfect equality: x% of people get x% of income.</li>
        <li>The Lorenz curve lies below equality when income is concentrated at the top.</li>
        <li>The shaded area is what the Gini coefficient normalizes into a number between 0 and 1.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="lorenz-lens-note">If Lorenz curves cross, rankings can depend on the chosen inequality measure.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</figure>
